SIMPLE: effusive
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: effusive
<hw>ef*fu"sive</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Pouring
out; pouring forth freely.</def> <mark>[archaic]</mark> ⟦ldquo⟧Washed
with the <xex>effusive</xex> wave.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>Pope.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Geol.)</fld> <def>formed by an outpouring of molten
lava, or pertaining to rocks so formed.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>overly demonstrative; expressing emotion in an
unrestrained manner; exhibiting unrestrained enthusiasm; -- of people
and human actions; <as>as, <ex>effusive</ex> thanks; an
<ex>effusive</ex> letter of recommendation</as>. Contrasted with
<contr>reserved</contr>.</def> <wns>[wns=1+2]</wns>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> gushing, gushy, burbling, burbly.</syn>
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Effusive rocks</b></col> <fld>(Geol.)</fld>, <cd>volcanic
rocks formed by a nonexplosive outpouring of lava in molten or plastic
form; in distinction from so-called <contr>intrusive</contr>, or
<contr>plutonic</contr>, rocks.</cd></cs></p>

<p>-- <wordforms><wf>Ef*fu"sive*ly</wf>, <pos>adv.</pos> --
<wf>Ef*fu"sive*ness</wf>, <pos>n.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>effusiveness</ent>⟦br⟧
